nd cyber domains. Fuelled by a deep curiosity about the command and its decisions made in the face of inevitable geopolitical and technological changes, this book uses a functional lens to evaluate NORAD’s options and the technological and organizational solutions needed to defend North America. The authors investigate the ways in which the NORAD command might adapt in the future as it struggles to modernize and keep ahead of new threats.This book comes at a critical time. The rise of new peer competitors requires a fundamental reconsideration of North American defence. As one of very few contemporary analyses of the command and its future, NORAD will be a vital tool for scholars and practitioners.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCommand and control systemsxTechnological innovationszCanada. 0aCommand and control systemsxTechnological innovationszUnited States. 0aGeopoliticsxHistoryy21st century. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Security (National & International).2bisacsh  a9/11.  aArctic.  aCANR.  aCanada.  aCanadian Armed Forces.  aCheyenne Mountain.  aContinental defence.  aNORAD modernization.  aNorth Warning System renewal.  aRCAF.  aUSA.  aUSAF.  aUnited States.  aaerospace control.  abinational agreement.  acommand.  acyber.  adeterrence.  afunctional theory.  ahypersonic weapons.  amaritime warning.  amissile.  aspace.1 aFergusson, James, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRobinson, Lori J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSt-Amand, Pierre J.J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978022801493540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780228014935423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780228014935/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles